            h2 Joseph Prosnitz
            p Joseph Prosnitz the entrepreneur behind Up-Ride has Crohn's disease and related Juvenile Arthritis (Ankylosing Spondylitis). Joseph does marathon and long distance triathlon to stay active. He developed Up-Ride to make run training less painful and more convenient during Chicago winters. Joseph and the Up-Ride team believe that people, especially the physically challenged (injury or chronic illness), deserve the health and happiness that exercise provides at a price they can afford.

            h3 Awards and Nominations for Up-Ride:
            li • Depaul University Business Plan Competition award of $5000 and audience choice award of $1000
            li • PresenTense JCC pitch competition awarded a $2500 award and a popularity prize of $250
            li • Completed government Self Employment Training (SET) and received a $1000 grant
            li • Runner up (4th) MIT Accelerate business competition in the product category (out of 50 plus) Awarded a go to market strategy analysis by a team of mba students.
            li • Finalist RedEye Chicago Newspaper competition in the design category, given studio time for filming
            li • Finalist Boca Bearings design competition given $500 in services as well as a prize package worth several hundred.
            h3 Current nominations and awards:
            li • Final 25 in the Infymaker ten $10,000 awards.
            li • Joseph is nominated for 30 under 30 for the Society of Manufacturing Engineers by Mark O'Brien the Chicago chapter (largest in the US) Chairman
            li • Also currently an applicant in several other competitions.
